                                        for 3 years, Mr. Albert became the Company Secretary of a fast-growing Savings and
                                        Loan Institution in 1993.<br><br>
                                        From there he joined the Coscharis Group in 1994 and rose to the position of
                                        General Counsel in 2000. He quit paid employment to become an entrepreneur in
                                        2003, after co-founding Eagle Eye Communications, advertising, and branding
                                        agency responsible for several brand positioning at that time. He eventually
                                        co-founded Legalpedia in 2005. Legalpedia is the most comprehensive electronic
                                        library of legal resources in Nigeria. He is also a Senior Partner in Keystone
                                        Attorneys, an ICT-driven law firm based in Lagos.<br><br>
                                        Mr. Albert is currently the Editor-in-Chief of Legalpedia and also a Consultant to the
                                        United Nations on Justice Sector Reforms. He has trained several lawyers, law
                                        teachers, law students, and judges on the use of ICT in the legal profession. He led
                                        a team of Judicial officers to Singapore in 2012 on an UN-coordinated study tour
                                        sponsored by the Royal Kingdom of the Netherlands.<br><br>
                                        Mr. Albert has undergone technological training in the USA, Dubai, Singapore, and
                                        leadership training at the Lagos Business School. He holds a Master’s degree in Law
                                        and is a Director in several companies, including servicing companies in the Oil and
                                        Gas sector, where he consults as an expert in Local Content.
